# Obsidian Documentation Rules

> Config = `project-config-local.mdc` Variables tables. Replace `${VARIABLE}` with values from config. Use `PREFIX_*` or `[Section]` for groups.

## CONSTRAINTS

**CRITICAL**:
- Use MCP server for vault operations when available (see `mcp-rules.mdc` for MCP server details)
- Create bidirectional links between related documents

**MANDATORY**:
- Create files only in `${DOCS_PATH}/` and subdirectories
- Use Wikilinks for internal links: `[[Document Name]]`
- Use YAML frontmatter for metadata
- Use standard file tools with Obsidian-compatible formatting as fallback when MCP unavailable

**RECOMMENDED**:
- Use aliases for readable links: `[[Document Name|Display Text]]`
- Create index documents for grouping related materials
- Remove temporary files after use

## Link Syntax

| Type | Syntax | Use case |
|------|--------|----------|
| Basic | `[[Document Name]]` | Internal links |
| Alias | `[[Document Name\|Display Text]]` | Readable links |
| Section | `[[Document#Header]]` | Link to header |
| Block | `[[Document#^block-id]]` | Precise links |

## Document Structure

```yaml
---
title: Document Name
tags: [tag1, tag2]
created: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

## Obsidian Elements

- **Callouts**: `> [!note] Header` + `> Content`
- **Tasks**: `- [ ]` (pending), `- [x]` (completed)
- **Tags**: `#backend`, `#frontend`, `#deployment`

## Document Relationships

Create relationships between documents within same task:

| From | To | Link Type |
|------|----|-----------|
| Plan | Checklist | `[[checklist-*]]` |
| Checklist | Guide | `[[guide-*]]` |
| Guide | Examples | `[[*.example]]` |

## Directory Structure

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `${DOCS_PATH}/` | General documentation |
| `${DOCS_PATH}/planing/` | Plans and checklists |
| `${DOCS_PATH}/code-examples/` | Code and configuration examples |

## Document Naming

**Format**: `<type>-<area>-<name>.md`

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `plan` | Plans and strategies |
| `checklist` | Execution checklists |
| `implementation` | Detailed implementation |
| `guide` | Guides and instructions |
| `spec` | Technical specifications |

| Area | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `backend` | Server-side (Django) |
| `frontend` | Client-side (widget) |
| `deployment` | Infrastructure |
| `system` | System components |
| `migration` | Migrations |
| `api` | API and integrations |

